8\%, especially the detection of DR for stars with α \&lt; 6\% is challenging. Finally, we applied our method to four differentially rotating Kepler stars and found close agreement with results from detailed modeling. {\textless}BR /{\textgreater} Conclusions: The method we developed is capable of measuring stellar rotation periods and detecting DR with relatively high accuracy and is suitable for large data sets. We will apply our analysis to more Kepler data in a forthcoming paper.},
