nearly every red giant. These measurements naturally classify the stars
into various populations, such as the red giant branch, the low-mass
(M/M ⊙ {\textless}{\textasciitilde} 1.8) helium-core-burning red clump, and
the higher-mass (M/M ⊙ {\textgreater}{\textasciitilde} 1.8) secondary clump. The
period spacings also reveal that a large fraction of the stars show
