turbulence is assumed to be anisotropic, due to the stratification, with
stronger transport in the horizontal directions than in the vertical.
The main difference with the former treatments by Zahn ({\textbackslash}cite\{Zahn1992\},
A\&A, 265, 115) and Maeder \& Zahn ({\textbackslash}cite\{Maeder1998\}, A\&A,
334, 1000) is that we expand here the departures from spherical symmetry
