to tackle the rapid phases of evolution. The system of partial
differential equations, which govern the transport of angular momentum,
heat and chemical elements, is written in a form which makes it ready to
implement in a stellar evolution code. Here the effect of a magnetic
field is deliberately ignored; it will be included in forthcoming
papers.

Appendices are only available in electronic form at
http://www.edpsciences.org},
